Key Match Events: De’Aaron Fox poured in a game-high 29 points and recorded a double-double with 10 assists.
Domantas Sabonis recorded a double-double with 11 points and 10 rebounds.
The Sacramento Kings outscored the Phoenix Suns 29-14 in the final nine minutes.
The decisive run began with a 12-0 burst that featured 3-pointers by Kevin Huerter and Keon Ellis.
The Kings outshot the Suns 64.1 percent to 37.1 percent.
Josh Okogie had 25 points off the bench to pace the Suns.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Kings ran up their largest margin of victory this season.
The Suns were playing their second game in two nights.
